What Is Java?

-> Java is programming language
-> Java was developed by sun microsoft systems in 1995, later acquired by oracle corporation
-> James Gosling is known as the father of Java. 
-> Before Java, its name was Oak. Since Oak was already a registered company, so James Gosling and his team changed the Oak name to Java.
-> Java is used to develop mobile applications, desktop applications, & games and much more
-> Java is one of the most popular programming language in the world

It is used for:

-> Mobile Applications (Specially Android apps)
-> Desktop Applications, Web Applications 
-> Web Servers and application servers
-> Games
-> Database connections 
-> And much more

Why use Java?

-> Java works on different Platforms (Windows, Mac, Linux, Respberry, Pi, etc.)
-> It is used to learn and simple to use
-> It is open source and free
-> It is secure, fast and powerful
-> Java is an object oriented programming lanuage which gives a clear structure to programs and
	allows code to be reused, lowering development cost.
-> As Java is close to C++ and C#

Literals:

Literals are fixed values that we can used directly in our program. 
For example, 5, -12, .5, 'c' etc.

Types of literals:

-> Integers
-> Floating point Literals
-> Boolean
-> Character Literals
-> String

Variables:

-> A variable is location in memory(storage area) to hold data.
-> To indicate the storage area, each variable should be given a unique name

